# A [[benevolent]] spirit as opposed to a [[cacodemon]] (an evil [[daemon]]).
*Agathodemon also Agathodaimon or '''Agathodaemon'''. A good spirit/demon that was worshipped by the ancient Egyptians. He had the shape of a serpent with a human head. The flying serpents or dragons venerated by ancient peoples were also called Agathodemons, or good genies. http://www.occultopedia.com/a/agathodemon.htm - 123k -

